<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,757,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,865,891]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Remarks.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gorochov" authorityYear="1986" box="[448,639,865,891]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[448,639,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Eumodicogryllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a subgenus of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gorochov, 1986)" baseAuthorityName="Gorochov" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Modicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1137,1300,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Modicogryllus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." pageId="10" pageNumber="237" pagination="3 - 15" refId="ref14109" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1986) New and little known Grylloidea (Orthoptera) from Middle Asia and adjacent territories. Proceedings of Zoological Institute of Academy of Sciences of USSR, 140, 3 - 15." type="journal article" year="1986">Gorochov, 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and later elevated as a genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Defaut, B." box="[550,701,901,927]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" pagination="107 - 112" refId="ref13913" refString="Defaut, B. (2001) Actualisation taxonomique et nomenclaturale du &lt;synopsis des orthopteres de france&gt;. Materiaux Entomocenotiques, 6, 107 - 112." type="journal article" year="2001">Defaut, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The species of the genus bear a clypeal suture which is shaped as an angle. At the beginning, Gorochov (
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[589,773,937,964]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" pagination="3 - 15" refId="ref14109" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (1986) New and little known Grylloidea (Orthoptera) from Middle Asia and adjacent territories. Proceedings of Zoological Institute of Academy of Sciences of USSR, 140, 3 - 15." type="journal article" year="1986">Gorochov, 1986</bibRefCitation>
) included 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[893,1242,937,963]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bordigalensis">
<emphasis box="[893,1242,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Eumodicogryllus bordigalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1275,1426,937,963]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Tartarogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burdigalensis">
<emphasis box="[1275,1426,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">burdigalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Latreille, P. A." box="[151,321,973,999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refId="ref14882" refString="Latreille, P. A. (1804) Histoire Naturelle, generale et particuliere, des Crustaces et des Insectes. F. Dufart, Paris, 424 pp." type="book" year="1804">Latreille, 1804</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tarbinsky, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Tarbinsky" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[334,847,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chivensis">
<emphasis box="[334,638,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Eumodicogryllus chivensis</emphasis>
(Tarbinsky, 1930)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chopard, 1968" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1968" box="[906,1334,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Tartarogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[906,1156,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Tartarogryllus vicinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard, L." box="[1165,1334,973,999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" pagination="273 - 290" refId="ref13806" refString="Chopard, L. (1968) Beitrage zur kenntnis der fauna Afghanistans, Gryllodea et Tridactyloidea. Casopis Moravskeho Musea Acta Musei Moraviae, 53, 273 - 290." type="journal article" year="1968">Chopard, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
into this genus. Then, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chopard, 1943)" baseAuthorityName="Chopard" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[306,768,1009,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theryi">
<emphasis box="[306,571,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Eumodicogryllus theryi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard, L." box="[588,759,1009,1035]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" pagination="170 - 244" refId="ref13482" refString="Chopard, L. (1943) Faune de L'Empire Francais. I. Orthopteroides de L'Afrique du nord. Librairie Larose, II. rue Victor-Cousin, Paris, pp. 170 - 244." type="book chapter" year="1943">Chopard, 1943</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was moved into this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov, A. V. &amp; Llorente, V." box="[1099,1424,1009,1035]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" pagination="95 - 139" refId="ref14289" refString="Gorochov, A. V. &amp; Llorente, V. (2001) Estudio taxonomico preliminar de los Grylloidea de Espana (Insecta, Orthoptera). Graellsia, 57, 95 - 139. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / graellsia. 2001. v 57. i 2.281" type="journal article" year="2001">Gorochov &amp; Llorente, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). But there is one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Weber, 1801" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1801" box="[434,776,1045,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Acheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis box="[434,624,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Acheta chinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, F." box="[631,776,1045,1071]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refId="ref15811" refString="Weber, F. (1801) Observationes entomologicae, continentes novorum quae condidit generum characteres, et nuper detectarum specierum descriptiones. Impensis Bibliopolii Academici Novi, Kiliae, 116 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8639" type="book" year="1801">Weber, 1801</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, that has been forgotten after it was misapplied synonymy (
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard, L." box="[159,333,1081,1107]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refId="ref13766" refString="Chopard, L. (1967) Gryllides. Fam. Gryllidae; Subfam. Gryllinae (Trib. Grymnogryllini, Gryllini, Gryllomorphini, Nemobiini). Uitgeverij Dr. W. Junk, Gravenhage, 213 pp." type="book" year="1967">Chopard, 1967</bibRefCitation>
; Cigliano, 
<emphasis box="[460,519,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">et al.</emphasis>
, 2021). We re-established this species name here and proposed two junior synonyms, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[240,422,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bordigalensis" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[240,422,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">E. bordigalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[429,533,1117,1143]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[429,533,1117,1143]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tarbinsky" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[587,721,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chivensis" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[587,721,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">E. chivensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[728,832,1117,1143]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[728,832,1117,1143]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, of it.
</paragraph>
